commitResults.messageTitle: Add retrieval of group in model for Add command
commitResults.messageBody:
When adding a student, the AddCommand object is now created with a dummy Group in the Student object.

This is done so that the AddCommand#execute stage will be the one to do the checking if the indicated group (with respective groupName) exists in the model or not. It will then search for within the model, and replace the group in the parsed student to the correct group object stored in the model. This is because this is the stage that should have visibility of model, not at the parsing stage.

Note that this behaviour relies on Group#isSameGroup only checking for whether groupName is equal.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add proper retrieval of group in model for Edit command
commitResults.messageBody:
When editing a student, the editStudentDescriptor is now given a dummy group.

Within createEditedStudent, then will the existing group with matching name be retrieved from the model. As a result, the function has changed to throw a CommandException and accept the model as a parameter.
Student directly exposes groupName and description of its group unnecessarily, and this is dependent on Group implementation. Decrease coupling

2nd TODO requires saving/loading of groups to be implemented first.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix student references in groups for Add, Delete and DeleteGroup
commitResults.messageBody:
Add command will add a student to the indicated group
Delete command will now also remove a student from the group they belong to
DeleteGroup command will now remove all students associated with that group

Adding a student now adds a reference to it to the group it is assigned
Deleting a student now deletes a reference to it from the group it was in
Deleting a group now deletes all students inside the group as well
